Shonka Dukureh, who played Big Mama Thornton in the new Elvis biopic, has died at the age of 44. According to reports, the actress was found dead on Thursday morning in the bedroom of her Nashville apartment, which she shared with her two young children. TMZ reports that police informed them that one of her children found her and alerted a neighbour who called emergency services.Police say there is no foul play suspected and investigators are awaiting autopsy results before they can determine a cause of death.Shonka’s death comes just a month after the release of Baz Luhrmann’s highly-anticipated Elvis movie. As well as her role in the blockbuster, her vocals also feature in Doja Cat’s new single, Vegas. READ MORE:Kate Garraway pulls out of GMB as husband Derek takes 'turn for worse'  “Was a true honour getting to know her and I am so grateful to her for lending her incredible vocals to Vegas. “Her amazing performance in Elvis amongst her other artistry will live on. Sending my deepest condolences to her loved ones.”  Following her death, tributes have flown in from those who knew and respected her. Nashville Mayor John Cooper tweeted: “My deepest condolences to the family of Shonka Dukureh. “Shonka graduated from Fisk University and called Nashville home for many years. Her powerful voice and artistry will live on through her music, and we honour her memory on this sad day.” User @layhercake penned: “Shonka Dukureh passing away is so heartbreaking. More than just a beautiful voice...she was a mom to 2 babies. Lord, please wrap her babies and loved ones in love and healing.” Lauren added: “Shonka Dukureh had such a bright future ahead of her man. This is so sad.”